cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.DC 

This paper deals with energy management in communication systems, specifically in Coordinated Multi-Point (CoMP) systems powered by smart grids. It involves optimization techniques and algorithms for joint energy trading and communication cooperation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with cooperative behavior among base stations, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
